Introduced
Second Regular Session 124th General Assembly (2026)
SENATE RESOLUTION ____
MR. PRESIDENT:
I offer the following resolution and move its adoption:
1 A SENATE RESOLUTION honoring Dan Huge upon his
2 retirement.
3 Whereas, Serving most recently as Public Finance Director
4 for the Indiana Finance Authority until his retirement on
5 January 2, 2026, Dan Huge has devoted decades toward
6 strengthening Indiana's financial foundation;
7 Whereas, During his time with the Indiana Finance
8 Authority, Huge was integral in helping the state maintain its
9 AAA bond credit rating;
10 Whereas, Prior to joining the Indiana Finance Authority,
11 Huge worked as the Chief Financial Officer for the Capital
12 Improvement Board of Managers (CIB) of Marion County,
13 which owns Gainbridge Fieldhouse, Victory Field, and both
14 owns and operates Lucas Oil Stadium and the Indiana
15 Convention Center;
16 Whereas, Huge also served as the Executive Director for
17 the Indiana Bond Bank, which issues long- and short-term debt
18 obligations for local units of government, schools, and libraries
19 in Indiana; and
2026 RR 3517/DI JR

2
1 Whereas, Throughout his career, Huge remained focused
2 on serving Indiana by securing the best possible financing
3 outcomes for communities across the state: Therefore,
4 Be it resolved by the Senate of the
5 General Assembly of the State of Indiana:
6 SECTION 1. That the Indiana Senate honors Dan Huge
7 upon his retirement and thanks him for his service to the state
8 of Indiana through his career.
9 SECTION 2. The Secretary of the Senate is hereby directed
10 to transmit copies of this Resolution to Dan Huge.
2026 RR 3517/DI JR

